The JIRA SOAP API does not provide the user with a way to download attachments.  Different forums suggested building the download URL (i.e. https://server:port/secure/attachment/attachmentId/attachmentFilename).  However, this will give an access denied over SSL requiring the user to log in (even though they already logged in through the SOAP API).

It would be great if there was a way to download the attachment through the API using the token generated at login (the same token passed when calling most of the funcitons).

If there is already a way to download attachments without having to build the URL (or passing the username/password in the URL as some forums suggested), please let me know.  Otherwise, please consider adding this feature to the API.

