If the custom field have the name "progress", JIRA will generate warnings in log, for example:
{noformat}
2010-09-02 20:09:51,215 http-8080-Processor21 WARN kahloun.foong 72588x127x1 8r889p http://localhost:8080/secure/admin/CreateCustomField.jspa [issue.search.managers.DefaultSearchHandlerManager] A custom field 'Progress (Cascading Select)' is trying to register a clause handler against a system clause with name 'progress'. Ignoring request.
2010-09-02 20:09:51,223 http-8080-Processor21 WARN kahloun.foong 72588x127x1 8r889p http://localhost:8080/secure/admin/CreateCustomField.jspa [issue.search.managers.DefaultSearchHandlerManager] A custom field 'Progress (Cascading Select)' is trying to register a searcher against a system clause with name 'progress'. Ignoring request.
{noformat}
The name "progress" seems to be an important system clause. JIRA should prevent creating custom field with name "progress". It is tested to be happening in JIRA 4.0 till JIRA 4.1.2

